Iran Says It Broke Up CIA-Run Espionage Network, Aftab Reports

-- B y   L a d a n e   N a s s e r i
-- 
2011-05-22T08:43:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-22/iran-says-it-broke-up-cia-run-espionage-network-aftab-reports.html
Iran ’s Intelligence Ministry said it
dismantled a spy network run by the U.S. Central Intelligence
Agency and arrested 30 people it alleges are linked to the U.S.
intelligence services,  Aftab  newspaper said.  Iran’s Intelligence Ministry said the spy network aimed to
collect information on the Persian Gulf country’s research
institutes, universities, nuclear activities and defense
industry, according to a statement that was published in the
Tehran-based Aftab newspaper.  The Swiss embassy in Tehran, which represents U.S.
interests in Iran, said it wasn’t able to comment on the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ladane Nasseri in Tehran at 
 lnasseri@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 